We all loved the movie, no disappointment

This was a much anticipated movie in our household and it didn’t disappoint! It was fun and the pace went quick enough to hold both the attention of kids and adults alike. It wasn’t plagued with any moments that had you just wishing the story would progress or the movie would end. Josh Gad did his job of providing the comic humor and his character Olaf provided quite a good amount of laughs especially with his “one-man-show” recaps. I wouldn’t say it was as good as the first movie but it was definitely enjoyable. One downfall to the story is that it doesn’t give much closure in the death of Anne and Elsa’s parents or really explain WHY Elsa has powers. Overall a great movie that is definitely worth it to see!

Although I rarely think so highly of sequels, Frozen II was worthy of its name. With stunning visuals, a great soundtrack, an intriguing storyline, and enough funny moments to make a grown man cackle, this movie is a definite must see.

After watching Frozen II the second time, some reviews say there is no villain in this movie but it is just quite difficult for human to see themselves as the villain who destroy the balance of nature and the earth. So yes, we are the villain in the real world while the current administration just keep the blind eye reversing the efforts to save the earth and environment, we must do the next right thing! #NoTrumpAfter2020
